<j:jelly xmlns:j="jelly:core">
  <h2>Filtering the extended job history</h2>
  <p>
    This API endpoint supports filtering the build history by various parameters. You can use query parameters to specify your filters. For example:
    <ul>
      <li><code>status</code>: Filter builds by their status. Possible values: <code>all</code>, <code>SUCCESS</code>, <code>UNSTABLE</code>,
        <code>FAILURE</code>, <code>ABORTED</code>
      </li>
      <li><code>agent</code>: Filter builds by agent that exactly matches the given name. Use <code>built-in</code> to search for runs that used the controller.</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <h2>Limiting the number of results</h2>
  <p>
  By default only the first 100 builds are returned. You can adjust this using the <code>limit</code> query parameter.
  </p>
  <h2>Example</h2>
  <p>
    To retrieve the last 50 failed builds that ran on agent "agent-1", you would use the following API call:
    <br/>
    <pre>GET /job/&amp;lt;job-name&gt;/extendedBuildHistory/api/xml?status=FAILURE&amp;agent=agent-1&amp;limit=50</pre>
  </p>
</j:jelly>